HEADWORD: Sea orange
<hw>Sea" or"ange</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large
American holothurian (<spn>Lophothuria Fabricii</spn>) having a bright
orange convex body covered with finely granulated scales. Its expanded
tentacles are bright red.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea-orb</ent>⟦br⟧
